Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
EDUCATIONAL & POLITICAL EPICENTER
Downtown Tallahassee is the state’s political epicenter, drawing in visitors from around the state and nation each year to visit the Capitol. Known for it’s beautiful parks, boutique hotels, unique dining, museums, arts, music, and natural resources, Tallahassee is a growing destination for development – business, entrepreneurship, ongoing education, and entertainment. 

Tallahassee is also one of the State’s premier centers of education. Home of Florida State University, Florida A&M University, and Tallahassee Community College, and a rich tradition of academic research & development, the area has a wealth of talent that further supports an intraneural environment and a strong workforce.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Located at the corner of South Monroe Street and Jefferson Street at the heart of Downtown Tallahassee. Across the street from the Capitol Building and next door to the Leon County Courthouse.
